OL,3,CStarmer says UK will 'not support'
OL,4,CTrump's blockade of the Strait of
OL,5,CHormuz
OL,7,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,8,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,9,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,10,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,12,FAddressing the president's threats in
OL,13,Fthe immediate aftermath on Sunday, a
OL,14,Fgovernment spokesperson said: "We
OL,15,Fcontinue to support freedom of
OL,16,Fnavigation and the opening of the
OL,17,FStrait of Hormuz, which is urgently
OL,18,Fneeded to support the global economy
OL,19,Fand the cost of living back home.
OL,26,@vD@_OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1776172268
OL,3,CStarmer says UK will 'not support'
OL,4,CTrump's blockade of the Strait of
OL,5,CHormuz
OL,7,F"The Strait of Hormuz must not be
OL,8,Fsubject to tolling.
OL,10,F"We are urgently working with France
OL,11,Fand other partners to put together a
OL,12,Fwide coalition to protect freedom of
OL,13,Fnavigation."
OL,15,FThe prime minister had previously
OL,16,Faddressed the situation in the Strait
OL,17,Fof Hormuz, saying he had discussed
OL,18,Fviable ways to keep it open with
OL,19,FPresident Trump.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
